FOUR BYES! This one spins sharply and surprises everyone. Lyon gives it a bit more air and flights it on middle and off. Abdullah Shafique looks to press forward and defend but the ball turns sharply, goes past the pads and races away into the fine leg fence.
Around off, this is pushed out towards covers.
On middle this time, flicked away towards short mid-wicket.
Around off again, looking to pitch it on the rough. Shafique leans forward and keeps it out on the off side.
Slightly flighted, on a length and outside off. Shafique presses forward to defend.
This is spinning in from outside off. Ali gets behind the line of the ball and pushes it out towards covers for a quick single.
Ooohhh...nearly deceives the batter in flight! Mitchell Swepson gives it a good toss and lands it full around off, Abdullah Shafique skips down the track and then has to reach out in defense.
Loopy and full, around leg, Abdullah defends it towards mid on.
Extra loop on this delivery but it ends up to be overpitched, Azhar drives it through the gap at covers for a single.
Quicker through the air, a bit short and on middle, Ali defends it from the back foot.
Flight again, full around leg, it's worked in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Floated delivery, full and around off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and defends it back.
Flighted again, full and around off, defended back.
Uses his feet to this full ball and pushes it defensively towards silly mid on.
Flighted and full around off, Azhar presses forward in defense.
Loopy and full around off, this time Ali defends it from the middle part of his blade.
Quicker and fuller around off, Azhar defends it from the outer half of his bat to covers.
A touch short and on off, turning in, Abdullah Shafique goes back and forces it down to long on for a run.
Flatter again, short around off and spinning, Azhar Ali allows it through to the keeper. Maiden!
Slightly short and on off, Ali goes back and punches it to covers. Abdullah Shafique wants a run but he is sent back. Marnus Labuschagne misfields a bit but no run is taken.
Flighted around leg, it's defended down easily.
Loopy and full, around leg, Azhar Ali leans forward and defends.
Another one served quicker through the air, full and around leg, it's clipped to square leg.
Quick through the air, short and outside off, Ali cuts it from the back foot but finds point.

Drinks! It's been a solid opening hour or so for the hosts as Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali have added 39 runs and have gone past the individual 50-run mark as well. The hosts will expect more of the same from these two and hope they go into the Lunch break unscathed. Australian bowlers have been decent and Pat Cummins did bowl a probing line at the start of the day but they have not been able to trouble the batters at the crease as much as they would have liked to. They need inspiration from somewhere to break this stand before the interval.
Floated and full around off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and defends it ahead of his front pad.
FOUR! Poor length from Lyon and it's punished. He drags his length short and serves it around off, Abdullah Shafique goes deep inside the crease and slaps it to the cover fence.
Fuller and outside off, excellent line, Abdullah Shafique shimmies down the track a bit as he defends.
Flighted and outside off, Abdullah Shafique gets forward and across as he defends it on the leg side.
Tossed up, it's full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique uses his feet and drives it to point.
Loopy delivery, full and outside off, Azhar Ali leans forward and eases it down to long on for a single.
Nathan Lyon switches ends now.
Floated and around off, pushed from the back foot to covers.
Short and wide outside off, cut straight to point.
Quicker one, flat and short around leg, Ali nudges it through square leg for a run.
A touch short in length, around leg, Abdullah goes on the back foot and works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy and around leg, full in length, Abdullah again defends it safely.
The leggie begins with a full ball around leg, Abdullah Shafique is forward as he defends it back.
Very full and very wide, over 140 clicks. Azhar Ali shoulders arms but the ball dies on its way to the keeper.
Starc hits the length hard this time and bowls it a bit wide of the off stump. There is some away shape on it but Ali isn't going to play at that one.
Full and angled into off at 141.5 kph. Azhar Ali was ready to drive again but has to check his shot, in the end, to keep it out.
Starc goes full and wide again but delivers a low full toss this time. Azhar Ali reaches out to drive but gets it off the toe end of the bat towards the point region.
Full and wide, inviting the batter to drive but Ali leaves it alone.
On a nagging length, angled into middle but the ball just straightens a bit. Azhar Ali gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Around middle, this is nudged away onto the leg side by Shafique.
A bit shorter this time, at the stumps. Shafique goes deep in his crease and tucks it away towards backward square leg.
A bit flatter, on off. Shafique hangs back and defends it out on the off side.

Fifty for Azhar Ali at his home ground and it has been a really well-compiled knock from him thus far. Around leg, Ali strides forward and wrists it through the mid-wicket region for an easy single. This is his 35th Test fifty to go along with 19 centuries. It seems his family is there and it's always a great feeling to perform in front of your loved ones. Azhar thanks the heavens also as he raises his bat. A big hundred appears to be unlocking from his bat!
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Cheeky from Azhar Ali and that brings up the 100-run partnership between these two. This is pushed through, around off. Ali premeditates and fetches it as he plays the reverse sweep fine. The ball races away to the vacant third man fence. He moves to 49 now.

This is angled into middle and leg at 141 clicks and this time there's just a hint of reverse away from the batter. Shafique looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a bit early and gets a leading edge towards the cover region.
Full and close to the off stump channel. Shafique blocks it out from his crease.
FOUR! Top shot! Overpitched from Starc and Abdullah Shafique gets a good stride forward as he creams this one through extra cover for a glorious boundary.
A length ball, around 140 clicks and on off. Shafique flicks it towards mid-wicket.

Starc hits the length hard and angles it into the body. Abdullah Shafique's initial movement was to sway away from the line but then he realizes that it's approaching his body. He looks to fend it off but gets into an awkward position and he gets hit on the thigh pad. Starc appeals but he is the only one doing so.

This is speared in fuller from a bit wide of the crease and on the off stump line. Shafique hangs back and keeps it out towards the bowler. Starc just shows a bit of aggression as he pretends to throw it back onto the stumps, trying to catch out the striker.
A tad flighted, around leg. Shafique uses his feet and works it through the mid-wicket region for one.
Shafique looks to use his feet this time but Lyon just drags back his length a touch. Shafique pushes it back to the bowler.
Quicker again, on middle. Blocked out.
Lyon comes from 'round the wicket and angles it across the off stump, a little bit quicker. Shafique nudges it towards mid-wicket.
On middle, Ali turns it through square leg and picks up an easy single.
This is tossed up a bit, on off. Azhar Ali presses forward and blocks it off.
Time for some spin! Nathan Lyon is into the attack now. 0 for 15 in his 8 overs so far.
Fuller delivery, on the fifth stump line. Abdullah Shafique leans in and pushes it towards covers.
Full again, at 144 kph and around off. Shafique squeezes this one out towards point.
This is speared in full and around off, reversing away a bit. Shafique defends it out solidly.

Shout for an lbw! Not given and Pat Cummins takes the DRS. Looks to be missing the leg stump. It's indeed missing the stumps, confirms the Ball Tracking. Mitchell Starc angles this one in full and attacks the pads of Shafique. Shafique looks to flick it away on the leg side but the ball skids through and raps him on the pads. There is an appeal but only Starc seems interested. They do go upstairs and everything is in line but as it looked at first glance, it's sliding down and missing the leg stump. Australia have wasted a review, two in total, and Shafique stays unbeaten.

FIFTY FOR SHAFIQUE! It's a nice shot. Starc overpitches this time, around off, Abdullah Shafique drives it down the ground, beats mid off and collects a couple. Yet another excellent knock from Shafique, he continues with his fine form.
Beaten! Starc speeds in from 'round the wicket and delivers it around off at 134 clicks. The ball lands and straightens a hint as Abdullah Shafique is caught pushing and missing inside the line.
First bowling change of the day as Mitchell Starc comes in to replace Pat Cummins.
Started the over with a yorker and ends it similarly. Green hits the yorker mark around off at 138.9 kph, Ali digs it out to covers.
Fractionally short and around off, at 138.3 kph, Azhar goes on the back foot and plays it down to point.
In the channel outside off, holding its line, Azhar leaves it.
At 134.5 kph, Cameron Green delivers it on a length around off, Ali is solidly behind the line as he blocks.
Serves this one on a good length around off, a hint of inward shape, Azhar covers the movement and shoulders arms.
Beautifully bowled. A yorker around off at 138 kph, trying to catch the batter off guard, Azhar Ali though gets his bat down in time as he digs it out to safety.
On a length around off, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Pat Cummins spears in a very full ball around off, reversing in at 139 clicks, Abdullah Shafique brings his bat down and keeps it out on the leg side, from the inner half of his blade.
Solid. Full and around off at 134.8 kph, Shafique defends it back past the bowler to mid off.
Goes fuller this time around off, angling in at 141.1 kph, Abdullah Shafique helps it on the leg side, towards mid-wicket.
Beats the bat! Cummins speeds in and serves it close to off. The ball lands on a fuller length and moves away late. Abdullah Shafique has a tame push inside the line and misses.
Fuller in length and around off, Abdullah Shafique is solidly behind that one as he defends it out towards mid on.
Just a touch short and around off, at 137.3 kph, Azhar gets behind the line and blocks.
Plenty of movement on this delivery but it's served outside off. Azhar leaves and it goes swinging to the keeper.
Fuller and on middle, Azhar covers the line and defends it back.
Well played! Back of a length, outside off, Azhar plays late and guides it down to third man. Steven Smith chases it down from first slip and the batters take two.
Full and around off, defended off the front foot.
On a good length around off, defended to the off side. Called a no ball for overstepping.

FOUR! Lovely wristwork! Cameron Green is a little too straight with his line, the length is full and Azhar flicks it beautifully through the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary. Australia leaking a few boundaries this morning.
It's very full and around off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it back to the bowler. Pat Cummins collects and mimes a throw at the batter. The skipper showing some aggression.
Cummins goes fuller and around middle, Abdullah Shafique flicks it stylishly but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it towards the short cover fielder.
Delivers it on a length around off, it's blocked out on the off side.
FOUR! Fine shot! Back of a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique hangs on the back foot and punches it behind square on the off side for a boundary - third this morning. Shafique moves to 49!
Lands it on a length around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the back foot.
Fuller in length and on off, it's defended watchfully to the off side.
Bouncer around off, Azhar sways away from the line with good technique.
Back of a length, around off but staying low, Azhar is on his toes as he keeps it out to mid on.
Full and on middle, angling in, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.

EDGY FOUR! Two boundaries for Azhar but this was a bit nervy one. Green gets this one to reverse back into the right-hander, from around off. It's full and staying low, Azhar tries to defend but it takes a soft outside edge and goes behind. Doesn't carry to the keeper or the first slip fielder and shoots through the gap to find the fence at third man.
FOUR! Nice way for Azhar Ali to get going! Full and straying down the leg side, Ali picks it up off his pads and deflects it neatly down to fine leg for a boundary.

Cameron Green to partner Pat Cummins from the opposite end. So far, Green has figures of 7-2-17-0. There's a bit of a halt in play as the spectators continue to move around behind the sightscreen. It's all good now and play can continue.
Day 3 begins with a maiden! Around off and on a length, Abdullah Shafique is forward as he pushes it defensively to covers.
Fuller again and closer to the off stump line, Abdullah Shafique is solid in his front-foot defense.
Makes the batter play! Full this time, angling in around off, Abdullah Shafique is on the front foot as he brings down a straight bat in defense.
Pat Cummins keeps it in the channel outside off, on a length and there is a hint of reverse on this delivery, Abdullah Shafique is quite content in leaving it.
This one keeps a shade low. On a length and outside off, once again Abdullah Shafique makes a leave. No movement on this occasion.
Movement straightaway for Cummins. He lands it on a good length outside off, Abdullah Shafique offers no shot and it shapes away.

We are all set for play on Day 3! The umpires make their way out to the middle followed by the Australian players. The overnight batters for Pakistan, Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali walk out and the former will be on strike. The skipper, Pat Cummins has the ball in hand and is raring to go.

Pakistan at the moment sit in a comfortable position with just one wicket lost and Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali playing really well. But they need to stay focused and make sure they play out the first session with a minimum casualty in order to have a firm grip on proceedings. They need to bat through the whole day in order to surpass the Australian total and go into the final two days with a lead. So, which team will make use of the morning session and press the issue? Action on Day 3 starts in a bit. Don't go anywhere.

Australia will be a tad disappointed at the end of Day 2 as they could have got more than 450 runs and then with the ball, they just didn't get much reverse and could pick up just the solo wicket. They still have a sizeable lead of 301 runs and if they get a couple of early wickets on Day 3 then they can regain the advantage. Their spinners might come into play today so Mitchell Swepson and Nathan Lyon will be itching to perform.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 3 of the third and final Test match between Pakistan and Australia at the Gaddafi Stadium in Lahore. Day 2 proved to be quite exciting as at one point the visitors seemed to be running away with a very big first innings score but the hosts pulled it back nicely in the post-Lunch session and kept them under a score of 400. In the final session, Pakistan batted fairly well and have set up Day 3 nicely.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Right then! Day 3 is generally known as the moving day of a Test match and given the way things have panned out on Day 2, it surely will be an exciting day of cricket, with both sides looking to get ahead in the game. Pakistan will look to continue on their merry way and try to play out the whole day, getting close to or even surpassing the Australian total as they still trail by 301 runs. The visitors on the other hand will be looking for early wickets and Starc and Cummins will have to get the ball to reverse in order to do so. The spinners too might come more into play as the day goes on and it will be interesting to see how Swepson and Lyon approach the pitch and at what speeds do they bowl. It's make or break on the third day. The action will start at 1030 IST (0500 GMT). But as you all know you can join us early for the build up. Do join us then. Cheers!

Naseem Shah is in for a chat. He says, shifting from T20 to Test has not been easy, but as a professional bowler, he was always ready. Adds he focused on bowling fuller lengths and is glad that it worked out. Mentions, that was the whole plan and once the reverse came into play, he tried to make the most of it. Also, praises the effort of Shaun Tait as a bowling coach, who has helped him a lot to see an upward growth in his performances.

Given the way the second day started, the hosts will be pretty pleased to have ended the day with just one wicket lost and not staring down a first innings score of 450 plus. Pakistan had the momentum coming into the second day but the way in which Carey and Green attacked their bowlers, that advantage was wiped out completely. It was in the second session though when they pulled up their socks and went on an all-out attack. Nauman Ali got the crucial breakthrough by dismissing Carey and after that young pacer Naseem Shah and Shaheen Afridi worked their magic, getting the ball to reverse at will and soon cleaned up the tail, picking 4 wickets each in the innings. It was then a slow start with the bat by the hosts and Imam-ul-Haq fell early yet again. After that, Abdullah Shafique and local boy Azhar Ali added on 70 runs and kept the Australian attack at bay. They have now set a good platform and will look to press home the advantage on Day 3.

The Aussies were all over their opponents in the first session as Alex Carey and Cameron Green fended away the Pakistani pacers and scored runs as well. The pair added on a big partnership and went into the second session unscathed. The post-Lunch session though was a different story altogether and once Carey fell, Green couldn't hold on for much longer either and even though the tail added valuable runs, the visitors lost 5 wickets inside one session. Pat Cummins gave them a good start with the ball by dismissing Imam-ul-Haq in the 13th over but they have struggled to get the ball reversing like their counterparts and it has been pretty easy going for Pakistan. They will now look to come back stronger with the ball on Day 3 and try to take advantage of the cracks which have started opening up.

Session summary : 39 overs / 90 runs / 1 wicket. The deciding Test match of the series has moved along nicely on Day 2 with both sides looking to be a bit aggressive and go after the win instead of just looking to play out a draw. A total of 249 runs were scored in the day and 6 wickets fell as well. Day 2 has set up an interesting match that can go either way and all eyes will be on the morning session on Day 3 to find out which team nudges ahead in the Test match.
Length ball, outside off, nips in a bit. Abdullah Shafique strides and defends it to the off side. The batters take a single. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller, just outside off. Abdullah Shafique flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique punches it through covers for two runs.
Full length, outside off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to cover.
Full, with a hint of reverse on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it back to the bowler. Cameron Green collects it and throws it at the batter's end. Abdullah Shafique races away to the leg side.
Short ball, outside off. Ali leaves it alone.
Good length, wide outside off. Ali leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, angled down leg. Azhar Ali stays back, clips it to deep square leg for a brace.
Full, outside off, Ali defends it to the off side.
Full length, angled in on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it to cover on the front foot.
Full delivery that reverses into the pads. Abdullah Shafique flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it to cover for a single.
This one is swinging away, full, outside off. Abdullah Shafique bunts it to mid off.
Full length, tailing into the pads. Abdullah Shafique pushes it to mid on.
Good length, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it back with full face on offer.
A yorker length delivery, outside off, swinging away a touch. Azhar Ali digs it out to third man. They take a single.
Full length, angled into the pads. Azhar Ali defends it to mid on.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique clips it to mid-wicket.
Full and reversing into the off stumps. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to block it into the deck.
Good length, outside off, reversing from the fifth stump. Abdullah Shafique shoulders his arms at it.
Another good leave by Abdullah Shafique! Length ball, outside off, shapes in late. No shot offered.

On a length, outside off, this one goes away off the deck. Abdullah Shafique shoulders his arms with ease. The ball is pretty far away from the stumps, but it looks like the Australian skipper is making the most of the opportunity and puts up a great act, as if it was a whisker away.
Full length, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique blocks it back to the bowler. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Length ball, on fifth stump line. Abdullah Shafique defends it to mid off on the front foot.
Length ball, on the pads, Azhar Ali clips it to square leg.
Back of a length, nips in a touch late. Azhar Ali shoulders his arms at it.
Good length, outside off. Ali blocks it to the off side.
Full length, with a hint of reverse into off. Azhar Ali blocks it to cover.
Back of a length, on middle. Azhar Ali ducks under it.
Full length, it reverses into leg. Abdullah Shafique flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Full length, outside off. Azhar Ali looks to push it away from his body. It takes the outside edge and goes behind point. The batters take two runs.

Pat Cummins appeals yet again but this time Alex Carey is sure that the impact is outside the line. Full length, outside off, it shapes in a long way. Azhar Ali strides and tries to defend it out. He gets beaten on the inside edge and rapped on the pads. Impact outside off is the message from behind the sticks.
Good length, outside off. Ali taps it to point.
Good length, on the fifth stump. Azhar Ali shuffles across and shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, wide outside off. Ali leaves it alone for the keeper.

A good shout from Pat Cummins. He looks very interested and eventually takes the review. It is a length ball, angled down leg. Azhar Ali tries to flick it away but misses. He gets hit on his back leg. Pat Cummins appeals but the umpire is unmoved. He takes the review. The replays confirm the impact is outside leg. Australia lose a review this time.
Mitchell Starc is off the field for a breather and Pat Cummins comes back into the attack to replace him.
An inswinger, fuller, on the pads. Abdullah Shafique clips it to square on the leg side. A maiden for Cameron Green now.
Full length, outside off. It shapes in off the deck. Abdullah Shafique defends it to cover.
Length ball, on top of off. Abdullah Shafique defends it out watchfully.
The dots just keep creeping up. Full length, on the pads. Abdullah Shafique tries to flick it away, but is a bit early into his shot. It takes the leading edge and goes to the off side.
Good length, outside off, it nips in off the deck with some extra bounce. Abdullah Shafique blocks it to the off side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it to mid on.
Cameron Green (3-1-11-0) is brought back into the attack.
Three dots on the trot! Full length, outside off. Azhar Ali prods to defend it to cover. Australia continue to stem up the run flow.
This is tad short, angled down leg yet again. Alex Carey continues to work hard behind the sticks.
Full length, sliding down leg. Azhar Ali flicks it to mid-wicket for one more run.
Fuller, on middle. Azhar Ali flicks it through mid-wicket for two runs.
Full length, outside off. Azhar Ali steps across, defends it to cover.
Mitchell Starc comes 'round the wicket and spills it down the leg side. Azhar Ali leaves it alone. Alex Carey does well to gather the ball behind the sticks.
Flotaed, full, just outside off. Azhar Ali flicks it to the leg side for one.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Nice variation this time! Some ohhs and ahhs from the players around the batter. It is flighted, around off. It grips and turns away, as Abdullah Shafique prods to leave it alone.
Fuller, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Outside off, defended off the front foot.
Length, around off, turning away. Abdullah Shafique cuts it to the right of point. The fielder at point dives to that side to make a sharp stop.
On the pads, flicked straight to the man at short mid-wicket.
This is pushed full and wide, around 140 clicks. Ali isn't going to play at that one.
On middle, Ali hangs back and tucks it to square leg.
This is jammed into middle and leg by Starc. Ali manages to keep it out towards mid on.
This is slanted onto leg stump. Ali works it towards short mid-wicket.
Length angled in from wide of off and over 141 clicks. Ali nudges it onto the off side.
A bit of bite on this occasion. On a length, on off and turns away sharply. Shafique does well to keep it out.
FOUR! Really nicely played by Abdullah Shafique. On middle, Shafique gets inside the line of the ball and paddles it into the fine leg fence.
On the pads, nudged away towards square leg. No ball called for overstepping.
Slightly flighted, on off. Shafique blocks it off the front foot.
Around off, driven on the up towards cover-point.
On middle, flicked away leg side for an easy single.
Flatter delivery, on middle and this one keeps very low. Ali keeps his eyes on the ball and blocks it off.
Length again over 143 kph and angled into off. Shafique stays solid in defense.
Full, on the fifth stump line and just reversing away a bit at 141.6 kph. Shafique blocks it onto the off side.
Length again, a bit too straight this time. Shafique pushes it out in front of square on the leg side and picks up another brace.
Nicely bowled! Fuller in length, outside off. This is angled in but holds its line. Shafique makes a watchful leave.
A length ball, angled into off stump from 'round the wicket. Shafique stands tall and defends it out.
Full and wide, this is squeezed away nicely towards the point fence for a couple of runs by Shafique.

DRINKS! After losing Imam-ul-Haq. The second-wicket stand has recovered well for the hosts. They will now look to add on to the tally and remain unscathed till Stumps. Australia, on the other hand, have been brilliant with the ball. They missed out on a couple of occasions and would hope it doesn't prove to be costly. Maybe, Pat Cummins should get his pacers back into the attack. And yes he agrees. Mitchell Starc is brought back into the attack.
Here comes the wrong 'un. On middle, worked through mid-wicket for one more.
Short and wide, cut away off the back foot by Abdullah Shafique towards the point fence. Travis Head runs around from the cover fence, slides in and cuts it off. Two taken.
On middle, tucked away towards deep mid-wicket for one more. The Australian spinners still searching for a bit of rhythm here.
Drifted onto the pads, turned through square leg for one.
Quicker one, speared into middle and leg. Kept out by Shafique.

FOUR! Tossed up, around off. Abdullah Shafique dances down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and goes inside-out with the spin and clears extra cover with ease. The ball races away into the fence.
Full, around off. Blocked out.
Outside off again, Ali presses forward to defend but the extra bounce makes the ball hit the gloves.
Full and wide, pushed towards covers.
Nicely bowled! Quicker and flatter, turning in sharply off a length. Ali gets pushed onto the back foot but does well to keep it down towards backward point.
Fuller and outside off. Ali looks to drive but checks his shot in the end and defends it out.
Quicker one, spinning in from outside off. Azhar Ali gets a big stride forward to negate the turn.
Flatter and around off, cut away towards point.
On off, defended out.
Shorter, on middle and leg. Ali works it off the back foot in front of square on the leg side for a run.
This is bowled on off. Ali prods forward and nudges it on the off side. A bit of extra bounce on this occasion for Swepson.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely bowled! A touch quicker and on off. Shafique strides out to defend.
This is pushed a bit wider and Ali taps it towards point.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Ali defends it out.
FOUR! Well, that one slipped out of the hands for sure. This is dragged down the leg side. Azhar Ali rocks back and pulls it into the backward square leg fence.
A touch shorter and on middle and leg. Ali works it leg side.
Closer to the off pole this time. Ali blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Ali keeps it out on the off side.
On middle again. Shafique keeps it out.
On middle, blocked.
This is floated down the leg side. Shafique flicks it towards backward square leg.
Short again, outside off. This is dabbed down towards backward point.
This is banged in short and outside off. This is slapped away to sweeper cover for a single.

NOT OUT! Huge roar from the crowd when the decion comes up on the big screen. Nicely flighted, on a nagging length and around off. The speed of the ball is around 85 kph and this allows the ball to grip and turn a bit. Azhar Ali reaches out to drive but gets undone in flight. Alex Carey whips off the bails but the replays show that Ali had got his back leg back inside the crease.

Is that stumped? Alex Carey seems confident and it has been taken upstairs. The catch will be checked first as it is close to the bat but UltraEdge shows there's no bat involved. The replays show that the foot is grounded before the bails come off and Azhar Ali survives.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller one, around off and it's quicker again. Ali pushes it down to long on and collects a single.
Around off, Azhar Ali gets a big stride forward to make the block.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Kept out on the off side by Ali.
Quicker one, at 91.6 kph and outside off. Ali gets behind the line of the ball to block.
This is sliding down leg, Ali tucks it away to short fine leg.
Good fielding! This is tossed up outside off. Abdullah Shafique with a firm cover drive but can't get it past the cover fielder. Mitchell Swepson starts off with a maiden.
A bit flatter this time, around off. Shafique cuts it towards point.
This is flighted around middle and leg. Shafique works it onto the leg side.
Slower through the air, on middle and leg. Shafique stays solid in defense.
On off, blocked.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Shafique keeps it out.
Full, outside off. Ali prods to block it out.
On off, defended out.
SIX! BANG! A clean hit over the fence. This wakes up the crowd now. Fuller, on off. Azhar Ali comes down the track and smokes it over long on for a maximum.
Turning in, around off. Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Azhar Ali uses his feet and wrists it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, defended to short leg.
Full length, angled in, on fourth stump. Abdullah Shafique prods, defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Full, on fourth stumps. Abdullah Shafique blocks it to the off side.
Length ball, on the stumps, this one stays a touch low. Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly off the front foot.
Good length, angled into the pads. Abdullah Shafique tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on the fifth stump. Abdullah Shafique drives it along the ground back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played. A freebie honestly. Back of a length, sliding down leg. Abdullah Shafique tickles it fine for a boundary.
On the pads, Ali tucks it to mid-wicket. Just two runs off it. Nathan Lyon with another tidy over.
Angled down leg. Ali blocks it square on the leg side.
Full, on off stump. Ali goes back and defends it out.

A loud appeal but the umpire shows no interest! Tossed up, outside off. It grips and turns in. Azhar Ali lunges to flick it away but fails to get any bat on it. Nathan Lyon appeals but no interest. Going down leg.
Darted on the pads, Ali clips it through mid-wicket for a brace now.
Tossed up, outside off, turning in. Azhar Ali smotheres it out.
Nathan Lyon (3-1-2-0) is back into the attack.
Shortis, outside off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it to point.
Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it out.
Back of a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique sways away from the line.

FOUR! EDGY! Abdullah Shafique gets lucky this time. It is a good-length ball, on fourth stump. It generates some extra bounce off the deck. Abdullah Shafique is caught it to minds, whether to play it or leave it. He does the former. The ball takes the outside edge,pierces the gap between first slip and the wicket-keeper. A lucky boundary.
Full length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique defends it to cover on the front foot.
FOUR! Classic on drive! Touch fuller, angled in on off. Abdullah Shafique times it to perfection and drives it down the ground for a boundary.
Full, on off. Ali drives it to mid off.
Full length, outside off. Ali defends it to point.
A slow bouncer, down leg. Azhar Ali does not pick it up and ducks under. Although the ball sneaks down the leg side.
Good length, outside off. Azhar Ali leaves it alone. Wide called.
Full length, on off. Ali defends it to mid-wicket.
This one is spilled down the leg side. Azhar Ali leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a good length and over middle. Shafique hops back to defend.
Fuller ball, on off. This is played towards covers.
Length this time, on off stump. Shafique gets an outside edge down towards the gully region.
On off, this is squeezed through the cover region for a single.
Full, on the sixth stump line and at 140 clicks. Azhar Ali shoulders arms at it.
Pitched up, on off. Ali hangs back to defend it out.
On middle, tucked away straight to mid-wicket.
A length ball, slanting into middle and leg. Shafique works it towards mid on.
Full and angled into off stump. Shafique blocks it out.
Around the top of off. This is tapped towards the cover region.
Pitched up and this is pushed towards wide mid on for one more.
A length ball, angling down leg. Shafique flicks it off his hips towards fine leg for a single.

Lovely timing but it will only be a couple of runs. Fullish ball, outside off. Azhar Ali leans in and punches it through the cover region. Marnus Labuschagne gives chase from cover-point and keeps it down to a brace.
A bit too straight from Cummins and this is flicked down to fine leg for a run.
On middle, defended solidly off the front foot by Shafique.

Another excellent delivery from Cummins. This is angled into middle and the ball keeps a tad low. Azhar Ali pushes at it with hard hands and gets an outside edge past the slip cordon. The ball goes towards third man and Ali gets off the mark as well.
Pitched up on middle. Ali stays solid in defense.

Drinks! The Pakistani batters had made a watchful start and kept the Australian pacers at bay. But in the past 2-3 overs the ball has started to reverse a bit and Pat Cummins has got the big wicket of Imam-ul-Haq. This will make the start for Pakistan even slower and allow the Aussie to dictate a bit. The hosts will have to stay positive and not get bogged down or else one down can easily becomes 2-3 down very soon. Azhar Ali walks out to bat at number 3 in front of his home crowd for the first time ever.

OUT! LBW! What a move from the skipper! Pat Cummins brings himself back into the attack and gets the breakthrough straightaway. Cummins comes 'round the wicket and angles one in a touch fuller and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq looks to flick it leg side but falls over a bit and ends up playing all around it. He gets pinged on the pads and the finger is raised in a jiffy. Imam consults with Shafique but it looks adjacent and he doesn't review it. The replay shows that the ball was going on to hit the leg stump.
Shorter ball, on middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq works it off the back foot through square leg for a single.
Nicely flighted, on leg stump. Imam defends it out watchfully.
A bit of hesitation in the middle but Imam-ul-Haq gets back in time. Flatter, on middle and tucked away to mid-wicket. Imam wants the quick single but is sent back and rightly so.
Angled into middle, Imam defends it under the eye line.
Around off, this is worked past silly point.
Quicker and on off at around 93 kph. Imam prods and keeps it out towards silly point.
On off, blocked out onto the off side. Maiden!

Ooh, there might just have been an inside edge on that one. A tad fuller, around off and nipping back in a long way. Abdullah Shafique looks to cover drive but gets a big inside edge onto the pads. Cameron Green with a huge appeal but the umpire stays unmoved.
On a good length, over off. This is dabbed down to short mid off.
A length ball on off. Shafique pushes it out towards covers.
A good bouncer, over off stump. Abdullah Shafique is taken aback a bit but does well to sway away from the line.
Full and straight, kept out on the leg side.
Floated, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it to cover.
Length, just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it firmly to mid on.
Angled into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq block it watchfully.
Fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it on the front foot.
On off, Imam-ul-Haq strides and defends.
Angled in on off. Imam-ul-Haq prod and defends it out.
Full length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it to cover.
Length ball, outside off. Shafique blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length, outside off, nips in a touch late. Abdullah Shafique inside edges it onto his pads. The ball could've gone to hit the stumps, but Shafique is alert enough to deal with it.
NO BALL! Cameron Green oversteps on this occasion and the umpire signals a no ball. It is outside off, left alone.
Full length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it to cover on the front foot.
Good length, sliding down leg. Imam-ul-Haq helps it around the corner to long leg for a single.
Length ball, angled down leg. Abdullah Shafique flicks it off his pads to deep square leg for a single.
Full, on middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it to short leg off the front foot.
Angled into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out watchfully.
Floated, full, around middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique eases it down to long on for a single.
Fuller, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it to backward point off the outer half.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique defends it on the front foot.
Looped up, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Nathan Lyon to have a bowl now.
Fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to mid off.

FOUR! EDGY! The luck is in Pakistan's favour. Full length, on fourth stump line. Imam-ul-Haq tries to defend it out. The ball races away through the slip cordon off the outside edge. Another boundary.
Full length, on the pads. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Length ball, on off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off. This is kept out towards cover-point.
FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq welcomes Cameron Green to the bowling crease with a boundary. Full and outside off from 'round the wicket. This is delightfully driven through extra cover for a boundary.
First change in the bowling for Australia. Cameron Green comes in to replace Mitchell Starc.
Change.
Fuller, on the stumps. Shafique remains solid in his defense.
Some bounce! Length, on off, it flies off the deck. Abdullah Shafique defends it into the deck.

FOUR! EDGY! Oh nearly! It was a tough chance though. A length ball angled in, on top of off. Abdullah Shafique stays inside the crease, gets squared up. The ball takes the outside edge, goes past Cameron Green at second slip. Boundary.
A length ball, outside off, nips in a bit. Abdullah Shafique defends it to cover off the front foot.
Fuller, on the pads. Abdullah Shafique flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it to mid on with a straight bat.
Fullish ball, around off and driven off the toe end of the bat towards cover.
This is banged in short over middle and leg. Imam does well to duck under it and the ball doesn't quite carry to the keeper.
Full and straight this time from Starc. Imam-ul-Haq defends it with a dead bat.
Sliding onto the pada and this is flicked away nicely but straight to the man at square leg.
Around 144 clicks and over middle stump. Imam-ul-Haq defends it out.
A length ball, outside off. Shafique drives it on the up to the man at the cover fence for a single. He is off the mark now.
Length this time, on off. Imam hangs back and keeps it out on the off side.
On a driving length, outside off. Imam doesn't play at it.
Around the top of off, at around 140 clicks. Imam defends it off the front foot.
Good-length, around the fifth stump. Imam hangs back and nudges it down towards covers.
Fullish delivery, sliding well across the off stump. Left alone.
This is angled into middle and leg by Cummins. Imam makes a watchful block.
Around the hips, this is dabbed down towards square leg.
Full, on off. Blocked out solidly by Shafique.
A bit wide of off stump at 143 kph and left alone by Shafique.
Back of a length, at the body and around 140 clicks. Imam hops and tucks it away through square leg for a single.
Sliding down the leg side, Imam-ul-Haq looks to flick but misses. There is a stifled appeal from behind the stumps but maybe just brushing the pads.
Full and around off, shaping away from the left-hander. Left alone by Imam-ul-Haq.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Nipping back into leg stump again. Shafique gets hit on the pads again but it's still a bit too high.
On a good length, around middle and nipping back in. Shafique gets caught on the crease and rapped high on the pads.
Good length, on off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Back of a length, on the body. Shafique awkwardly keeps it out.
Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends it out.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end.
A bouncer to end the first over. Over middle and Imam-ul-Haq sways away from the line of the ball.
Better from Starc. Just full of a length, at around 142 clicks and on off stump. Imam stays solid in defense.
Starc spills it down the leg side yet again. This time Carey moves early that side and pouches it.
On a good length, over middle. Imam-ul-Haq hops back and keeps it down on the deck.
Pitched up, around off. Punched towards covers.

Starc starts off with a wayward delivery, way down the leg side and swinging further down. Alex Carey springs to his left and just about gets a glove on it. The batters get a bye and the Pakistani innings is underway.

We are ready for the FOURTH INNINGS! The Australian players make their way to the middle and they are followed by the Pakistani opening pair of Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique. Mitchell Starc has the new ball in hand and is raring to go. Let's go...

The hosts were made to toil in the field but things could have been a bit different. Early in the day, they did not go up for a caught-behind appeal. Then Naseem Shah cleaned up Khawaja but off a no ball. There were a couple of dropped catches as well and they can only blame themselves. They have now 121 overs to stay on the crease and somehow manage to draw the game, if not win it. It is a big ask as no team has batted for more than 107 overs in the fourth innings here at the Gaddafi stadium in Lahore. First, they have to make sure they get through the 31 over remaining today unscathed or at worst losing just one wicket to have any chance on Day 5 of drawing/winning the game. Babar Azam and his men did bat for more than 170 overs in the previous match but can they do it again?

Here comes the declaration! With the lead exactly 350 runs, Pat Cummins gives the signal from the balcony that they have batted enough. It has been a brilliant display of batting from Australia on Day 4 and all credit goes to their star batter of the series, Usman Khawaja who just keeps on notching up big runs. David Warner was prolific alongside Khawaja at the start of the innings as the pair added on 96 runs for the first wicket. Marnus Labuschagne too got the monkey off his shoulder and batted positively, adding a further 65 runs to the total alongside Khawaja. Usman Khawaja got to his century and Steven Smith took the record of being the fastest man to reach 8000 runs in Test cricket, in terms of innings. With a potent bowling attack that is high on confidence, the Aussies will feel they have a big chance of winning the match.
Floated and full, landing around off, spinning in, Head is forward as he defends it to the off side. Pat Cummins walks out of the dressing room and AUSTRALIA HAVE DECLARED!
FOUR! Flatter and shorter, outside off, Head hangs on the back foot and whacks it through cover-point for a boundary. The lead is 350. No declaration but it could be the last over.
SIX! Head has picked the bones out of that one. Loopy and full, landing around off and turning in, Head kneels and smokes it over mid-wicket for a maximum.
Fuller and on off, flicked on the leg side but straight to mid-wicket.
Flighted and full, landing outside off, Head tries to sweep but misses. He is hit on the pads but outside the line of stumps.
Sharp turn out of the rough outside off. Head guards his stumps and leaves it.
Bowls it short and close to off, Head slaps it to deep cover-point and opens his account with a single.
Travis Head walks out to bat at number 5.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Naseem strikes and is elated. Hurls it on a good length close to off, at 137.7 kph and it straightens just a hint after landing. Steven Smith has a tame push inside the line and gets a feather behind. Mohammad Rizwan collects a fine catch diving to his left, gets up to appeal and the finger goes up. Smith ain't sure and takes the DRS but the UltraEdge detects a spike. The lead for Australia is 339 runs.
