Flatter ball, outside off. Babar Azam taps it to the off side for a single.
Short of a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it to the off side.
Good-length delivery, around off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it out.
Full and down leg. Imam-ul-Haq misses his flick.
Short of a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it and dabs it onto the deck.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Babar Azam tucks it to the leg side and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Babar Azam blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq skips down yet again and defends it towards cover.
Imam-ul-Haq runs down the track to this length ball and tries to block it. The ball goes off the thick outside edge towards point.
Flattter ball, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.
Flighted delivery, on a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq dabs it onto the deck.
Tossed up, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.
Back of a length, around off. Babar Azam dabs it towards cover.
Good-length, around off. Babar Azam blocks it off the side.
Back of a length, around off. Babar Azam blocks it to the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is full and around middle. Babar Azam prods and caresses it through the mid on region for a boundary. Pakistan's skipper is off the mark in style.
On a good-length, around off. Babar Azam keeps it out.
Back of a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq taps it to cover and takes a single.
Touch fuller, much straighter now, outside off. Babar Azam leans and defends it out.
Sharp turn and extra bounce! Spinning in, around middle. Babar Azam stays in the crease and taps it towards square leg.
Tad quicker, outside off, full again. Babar Azam presses forward and defends it out.
Fuller ball, around off. Babar Azam leans and blocks it out.
Babar Azam, the skipper of Pakistan, comes to the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Australia opt for a review as they think Azhar Ali has got an inside edge before the ball pops out towards the first slip fielder who grabs it. It turns out to be a successful one for Australia as they get rid of Azhar Ali! Now coming to the ball - Lyon tosses it up, well outside off and spinning in late. Azhar Ali kneels to sweep but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball lobs up towards Steven Smith at first slip and he does the rest. The UltraEdge rolls in and it shows a slight spike. The third umpire asks the on-field umpire to reverse his decision. A huge blow for Pakistan as they lose their second wicket. AUSTRALIA BELIEVE!
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, outside off. Azhar Ali blocks it out.
Another top delivery by Starc! Another yorker, around off, at 144 clicks. Imam-ul-Haq does well to dig it out. A maiden over from him!
Full again, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq presents the full face of the bat and blocks it out solidly.
Well bowled! Yorker-length delivery now, around middle and off, at around 143 clicks. Imam-ul-Haq digs it out.
Full in length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Pitches it up again, outside off, tailing in. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it towards mid on.
Slower through the air, full, outside off. Azhar Ali presses forward and defends it out.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Azhar Ali defends it out.
Fraction short again, outside off. Azhar Ali pushes it towards point off the back foot.
Touch shorter again, around middle. Azhar Ali goes on the back foot and defends it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward and drives it past cover for a quick single.
Turn and bounce for Lyon! Fuller ball, spinning in, around middle. Azhar Ali stays in his crease and tucks it towards fine leg for a single.

DRINKS! Pakistan have added 30 runs to their total in the first session so far and both sides would be reasonably happy as the Aussies did manage to get rid of Abdullah Shafique early on. The pitch hasn't played much tricks, but the ball has just started to reverse, so the Pakistani batters would look to bat deep and keep the Aussie bowlers at bay. Also, the first session is going to be an extended one, which means it will go on till 1 pm IST (7.30 am GMT).
Very full, tailing back in, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it towards mid on.
Angling in, around middle, tad fuller. Imam-ul-Haq shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.

Another length delivery, tailing in, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq tries to block this but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat towards backward point. Once again, he wanted to sneak in a single but bails out at the end.
On a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it towards cover off the back foot.
Fuller ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Swinging in, tad fuller, on the pads. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards square leg. Imam-ul-Haq wanted a single there, but he decides against it in the end, as Azhar Ali wasn't interested to run.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Azhar Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
Touch shorter, outside off. Azhar Ali pushes it past the fielder at silly point.
Spinning in, fuller ball, around off. Azhar Ali defends it out from within the crease.
Quicker through the air, at around 89 clicks, fuller, around off. Azhar Ali leans and blocks it out.
Tad quicker, full, outside off. Azhar Ali gets down on his knee and looks to sweep this but he msses.
Close! A fuller ball, spinning in a tad, outside off. Azhar Ali leans to block but the ball goes off the under edge and it just goes past the off pole.
Down the leg side, on a length. Imam-ul-Haq looks to tuck this but he misses.
Full now, outside off, at 144.3 clicks. Imam-ul-Haq leans and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Better from Starc! This one was an outswinger, on a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq defends it out watchfully.
An inswinger, on the pads, fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it past square leg for a brace.
Another length delivery from over the wicket to the left-hander, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out watchfully.

Mitchell Starc serves a length ball from 'round the wicket, angling in, around middle, at around 139 clicks. Azhar Ali looks to block this but the ball goes off the outside half of the bat, away from the fielder at gully towards third man. Single taken!
Slower through the air, full and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq covers the line and blocks it with ease.

Nicely played! Flatter and quicker, on a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq hangs back and guides it past the short third man fielder for a brace. 100 comes up for Pakistan! They require 251 more runs to win this Test as well as the series.
Flighted delivery, around off. Imam-ul-Haq stretches forward and defends it. Not much spin for Lyon so far!
Lyon goes wide of the crease and serves it on a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, full and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off. Imam-ul-Haq gets forward and keeps it out.
Good-length delivery, around off. Azhar Ali blocks it with ease. 9 runs off the over!

FOUR! Edgy! But Azhar Ali controlled it nicely in the end. Back of a length, angling in and just shaping away a tad after pitching. Ali looks to sway his bat away from the line but in the end, manages to run it down past the slip cordon and into the fence. He made sure that he does not push hard at the ball and played it with soft hands.
Crunched but for no run! Another ball, full and outside off. Azhar Ali drives but Usman Khawaja at short cover dives to his left and stops it.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A half-volley, outside off from 'round the wicket. Azhar Ali prods and carves it through the cover region for a boundary.

FIFTY for Imam-ul-Haq! Another gritty innings by the Pakistani opener! This is a full ball, around leg. Imam glances it to fine leg and rotates the strike. Imam though would be aware that the job is only half done as Pakistan have a long way to go.
Starc starts with a wayward ball, angling down leg. Imam misses his flick and once again, Alex Carey has to make a diving stop behind the sticks.
Mitchell Starc (5-2-9-0) comes to bowl now.
Floated, full and outside off. Azhar Ali smothers the spin and blocks it.

Turn and bounce for Lyon! This is pitched way outside off. Azhar Ali looks to work it to the leg side with hard hands but the ball spins sharply and it goes off the inner half of the bat towards short fine leg.
Flighted delivery, around off. Ali defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on middle. Imam pushes it to mid on and scampers through to the other end. The fielder at mid on misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Floated, full and around off. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.

Lyon tosses it up, well outside off. Azhar Ali gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it through the cover region. The ball doesn't have enough legs to race away to the ropes. Pat Cummins cuts it off and the batters collect three runs.
It's time for spin! Nathan Lyon (9-2-23-0) comes into the attack.
Back of a length, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though. Another maiden over from Cameron Green!
Drags his length back a bit, around leg. Imam-ul-Haq hops in his crease and tucks it to square leg.
Green changes his angle and goes over the wicket. He hurls a full ball, on middle. Imam leans and drives it to the mid on fielder.
A length ball, jagging back in from middle. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and wrists it to mid-wicket.
A bumper, angling down leg. Imam-ul-Haq ducks underneath.
Green comes 'round the wicket and serves it on a length, around off. Imam gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it to the on side.
A length ball, jagging back in from off. Azhar Ali gets forward and defends it.
A short ball, around leg. Azhar Ali hangs back and tickles it to backward square leg.
Full and on middle. Azhar Ali drives but straight to the mid on fielder.

Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Azhar Ali skips down a bit and just guides it through the third man region. Mitchell Swepson gives it a chase and keeps it to just two. Good cricket all around.
On a length, around off. Azhar Ali keeps it out, off the front foot.
This is a full ball, angling in from off. Azhar Ali gets forward and pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, down leg. Azhar Ali tucks it towards fine leg for a single. He will keep strike for the next over!
Length delivery, angling in, around off. Azhar Ali leans to defend this but he gets an inside edge on the pads. Cameron Green though appeals for LBW, but the umpire is unmoved.
Pitches it up, around middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards mid-wicket and scampers through to the other end. A slight fumble there allows the batters to complete the run comfortably.
Touch fuller, angling in, around off. Imam-ul-Haq prods and blocks it out.
Down the leg side, length delivery. Imam-ul-Haq misses his flick.
Swinging in, around middle, on a length, at 133.3 clicks. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out.
Another length delivery, around middle. Azhar Ali shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Good-length delivery, around off, tailing in. Azhar Ali blocks it out towards point.
Tad fuller, around off. Azhar Ali pushes it towards mid off.
On a length now from over the wicket, around off. Azhar Ali defends it out off the front foot.

Leg bye! On the pads again, on a length. Imam-ul-Haq looks to tuck this one but he misses. The ball brushes off his pad and goes to the right of the keeper. This time Alex Carey manages to just a glove on it. The batters steal a leg bye as the ball rolls towards fine leg.
Angling in on a length from 'round the wicket, on the pads. Imam-ul-Haq tucks it towards square leg.
Down the leg side, on a length. Azhar Ali misses his flick. Alex Carey once again dives to his left and makes a good stop.
Shorter ball, outside off. Azhar Ali leaves it alone.
Very full, around middle. Azhar Ali defends it out watchfully.
Tailing in, on a length, around middle, at 136.1 clicks. Azhar Ali blocks it out.
A length ball from over the wicket, down the leg side. Azhar Ali misses his flick. Alex Carey dives to his left and pouches the ball.
Cameron Green goes 'round the wicket, serves a fuller ball, angling in, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it towards mid on and runs across to the other end.
Shaping in again, on a length, around off. Azhar Ali blocks it out towards cover. A maiden over by Pat Cummins!
Length, on middle. Azhar Ali blocks it out watchfully.
Another inswinger, on a length, around middle. Azhar Ali defends it out off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, jagging in, around middle. Azhar Ali defends it out.
Swinging in again, tad fuller, around middle and off. Azhar Ali defends it out.
Nipping back in, around middle, on a length. Azhar Ali blocks it out.
Full again, outside off. Azhar Ali leans to defend but the ball goes off the outer half towards third man. Single taken. Azhar Ali gets off the mark with that!
No Ball! Fuller ball, around off. Azhar Ali defends it out. Cameron Green has overstepped here. The umpire signals no ball.
Azhar Ali walks in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A massive breakthrough for Australia. This is just what Australia wanted heading into Day 5. They have broken this opening stand and have gotten rid of the in-form Abdullah Shafique. Pakistan lose their first wicket early on Day 5. This one was on a length, outside off, shaping away. Abdullah Shafique leans to block this but he manages to get an outside edge back to the keeper. Alex Carey takes an easy catch there. Cameron Green with the first wicket!
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter ball, down the leg side. Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but he misses.
Nipping back in, on a length, around middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it out off the front foot.
Beaten! On a length now, outside off, at around 129 clicks. Abdullah Shafique leans to block this, but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full, tailing back in, around middle and leg, at 133.4 clicks. Abdullah Shafique flicks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the front foot. Another maiden over!
This ball starts from well outside off and nips back in sharply after landing. Imam lets it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up, around off. Imam-ul-Haq leans and defends it to the off side.
Short of a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq covers the line and keeps it out. Not much movement for Australia's skipper.
Another ball, on a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the back foot.
Cummins bowls a length ball, around off. Imam gets behind it and dabs it onto the deck.
Slightly fuller, just outside off. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends it solidly.
Good-length ball, around off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.

This is a yorker-length ball, angling in late. Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but he misses and gets hit low on his pad. Cameron Green appeals but the umpire says no. Might have gone down leg, and hence, Cummins doesn't opt for a review.
On a length, around off. Abdullah Shafique defends it to the off side.
This is a length ball, outside off that jags back in sharply. Abdullah Shafique covers his off pole and leaves it alone. Lovely bowling from Green!
Full and around middle. Abdullah Shafique prods and flicks it to the square leg fielder.
Cameron Green (3-1-5-0) will bowl from the other end.
FOUR! Nicely timed by Imam! Cummins strays on the pads. Imam sits back and flicks it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. Pakistan are underway on Day 5!
On a length and well outside off. Imam does not bother playing at that one.
Cummins goes full and just outside off. Imam gets forward and drives it to the mid off fielder.
Good-length delivery, around off. Imam-ul-Haq gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
This is a length ball, around middle. Imam stands tall and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Cummins comes 'round the wicket and starts with a full ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq prods and pushes it towards mid off.
We are ready for action on Day 5! The players are out in the middle. Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq will resume their batting. Pat Cummins will begin with the ball. Two slips in place. Let's go...

Pakistan would be pleased to end the day without losing any wickets, but they still have a long way to go. They will be hoping to pile on more runs without losing many wickets in the first session. Although, it’s not going to be easy since there will some reverse-swing on offer which could prove to be threatening for the Pakistani batters. Stay tuned to see how the first session of the final day of this Test series pans out.

Australia were in a commanding position with a healthy lead by their side. However, they would be a little nervous coming into this final day since they were unable to break the opening stand at the end of Day 4. We did witness Pakistan crumble in the first innings and Australia will be hoping they can do the same. A few quick wickets and Australia would be on top.

Hello and welcome back, folks! We are now into the final day of the final Test of this exciting Test series between Pakistan and Australia. We have witnessed 14 days of thrilling Test cricket action in this series and it all comes down to this final day, where probably all results are possible. Both sides will be hoping they can bring out their A-game and come out on top.
... DAY 5, SESSION 1 ...

Right then! We have got a real contest on our hands and after 14 days of gruelling Test cricket it all boils down to this - 278 runs versus 10 wickets. Day 5 will begin on Friday at 10.30 am IST (5 am GMT) but the build-up will begin much sooner. Do join us for the fascinating final day. Till then, take care and goodbye!

Nathan Lyon looked really good with the ball and would want to hit the rough a bit more on Day 5 in order to create more chances. Talking about chances, the golden arm of Marnus Labuschagne almost got the breakthrough right before Stumps but once again Steven Smith was undone by the ball at first slip. At one point, the declaration seemed a good thing but having not picked up a single wicket so far, the Aussies will just be a little nervous coming into the final day of the Test match.

Australia will be a bit disheartened with that bowling performance but they still have plenty of runs to defend on the final day and given their performance in the first innings, the ball reversed pretty late in the innings. So, Mitchell Starc and Pat Cummins will still be a big threat for the opposition batters. They now have the dilemma to either press the issue early on the final day and take the risk of conceding runs or just stem the flow of runs and then attack later in the day.

The opening pair of Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique has remained rock solid in the final session and due to their efforts, this game hangs right in the balance. Imam and Shafique have added on 73 runs for the opening wicket and reduced the target well under 300 runs. This stand has made sure the hosts have a real chance on the final day of the Test match to not only save it but maybe to snatch the win off Australia's hands. They will have to bat patiently and put away the bad balls though if they do go for the win but Babar Azam will be fairly pleased with how things have ended on Day 4.

Drama right at the end of Day 4 but Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique have managed to remain unscathed! A total of 31 overs were bowled in the final session, with 98 runs being scored and just one wicket going down. Another fascinating day of Test cricket and with just one day remaining in the Test series, we still don't know which team is going to win or even for that matter if there's going to be a winner at all.
Loopy and full, around off, Abdullah Shafique presses forward and defends it watchfully. Stumps on Day 4!

EDGED AND FOUR! Yet another chance has gone past Smith at first slip. He has had a torrid time throughout the series. Loopy and around off, landing on a fuller length and spinning away, Abdullah Shafique cannot resist and goes for a full-blooded drive. It takes a thick outside edge, flies behind to slip where Steven Smith reacts to his right initially and the ball goes past the left side. It brushes his fingers and races behind for a boundary.
This one keeps low. Full and wide, outside off and spinning away, Abdullah Shafique tries to drive but misses.
Another delivery spinning away from outside off, Abdullah Shafique has nothing to do with it.
Turning away from the batter, from outside off, with some extra bounce, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.
Full delivery, flighted and around off, Abdullah Shafique drives it off the front foot to covers.
Pat Cummins has decided to toss the ball to Marnus Labuschagne for what is probably going to be the last over of the day.
Spears it in, very full and angling down the leg side at 141.9 kph, Imam tries to flick but misses.
Misfield! Fractionally short and outside off, Imam steers it down to point where the fielder fumbles and allows a couple of runs.
A surprise bouncer around off, at 135.5 kph, Imam-ul-Haq ducks immediately.
Lands it on a length and close to off, at 140.9 kph, Imam-ul-Haq crouches as he defends it back. That stayed low.
Fuller and on off, at 138.9 kph, Imam defends it down to mid on.
FOUR! Off the outside edge. Short in length and outside off, Imam stands back and flashes his bat at it. It takes the outer half and speeds down to the third man fence.

Green comes from over the wicket for the last delivery. Serves it short and angles it away from off, Imam cracks it to deep point for a single. 7 more minutes to go for Stumps, possibly two more overs coming.
Fuller and on off, Imam defends it ahead of his front pad and pushes it towards mid on.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it from the back foot to covers.
Again the length goes shorter, on off, Imam plays it down from the back foot to point.
Pitches it up this time, around off, bringing the batter forward who defends it cautiously.
Around off, on a good length and shaping back in, Imam stays back and punches it to covers.

The Pakistani batters are taking their time and very smartly slowing the game down as the 12th man runs onto the field with drinks and a new pair of gloves. The umpire Aleem Dar watches the situation quickly and tells them to hurry up as they will try to squeeze in as many overs as possible before the day ends.
Starc goes wide of the crease and spears in a length ball around off at 136.9 kph, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly again to covers. Maiden!
On a length and outside off, at 141 clicks, Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms.
Fuller and on off, defended back safely.
Starc goes very full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique squeezes it out to cover-point.
Darts it in, on a length around middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the back foot to mid-wicket.
Starc begins his new spell from 'round the wicket, eyeing some reverse swing. It's full and around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly to the off side.
Mitchell Starc (3-1-3-0) is brought back into the attack for a late burst. Can he get the ball to reverse swing and do a bit of damage?
Fuller and on middle, angling down, Imam flicks it from the middle of his bat but finds the square leg fielder. 17 minutes left on the clock for Stumps. 8 overs still remaining.
Keeps it on a length and close to off, angling in, Imam defends it from the back foot.
Back of a length, close to off, defended from the back foot to covers.
Close to off and a bit on the shorter side, Imam-ul-Haq tries to cut but ends up chopping it down. Luckily, he has not dragged it on.
A bit short and on middle, blocked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller in length and angling in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to the off side. In case a wicket goes down, Shaheen Afridi is getting ready to come out as a nightwatchman.
Flatter and a touch shorter on off, Imam goes back and whips it wide of mid on for a run.
Floated delivery, full and on off, it's defended ahead of the front pad.
Edgy! Good flight again from Lyon, he lands it full and outside off, getting it to turn away, Imam tries to drive but edges it down to third man. Green chases it down and they take two.
Nice flight on this one, full and around off, Imam pushes it off the front foot to covers.
Oohhhh...that keeps low from a shortish length around off, Imam gets back to cut and somehow keeps it out from the bottom edge.
Jumps down the track to smother the spin and defends it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up, full and around off, Abdullah Shafique leans forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. End of a harmless first over from Cameron Green!
Full in length, around middle and leg, Imam leans across and flicks it through the gap at square leg for a single.
Uses the angle of the bowler and wrists a length ball to square leg.
Around off, on a length, defended from the back foot.
Bouncers today have troubled the keepers more than the batters. Down the leg side and Carey has to dive to collect it. Called a wide for height!
All too easy at the moment for this pair. Short again from Green, outside off, Abdullah Shafique steers it down to third man for a single.
Fractionally short and close to off, Imam-ul-Haq goes back and taps it down to point for a single.
We are now going to see Cameron Green for the first time today. He replaces Mitchell Swepson in the attack and is ready to steam in.
Flatter and on off, Abdullah Shafique goes on the back foot and blocks.
Again the length is slightly short, around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the back foot, albeit from the inner edge.
Lyon comes from 'round the wicket but drops it short around off, Imam goes back and turns it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Lunges to a full ball and pushes it defensively in the gap at covers. They take a single.
Slightly short and outside off, Abdullah plays late and guides it towards point. Smith chases it from first slip and they decide not to cross.
Loopy and full, outside off and turning back in, Abdullah Shafique leans forward to defend but misses. He is hit on the front pad but outside the line of the stumps.
Nearly goes through. Sharp spin from the rough outside off, staying low as well from a shortish length, Imam does well to keep his eyes on the ball as he keeps it out safely to covers.
Puff of dust as it lands on a fuller length around off, Imam-ul-Haq stretches forward in defense.
Floated and around off, Imam-ul-Haq brings out the reverse sweep and sends it down to third man. Collects two. Under 300 needed now.
A touch short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique works it in the gap at square leg for a single.
Shortish and on off, punched off the back foot to the off side. Mitchell Swepson moved across to his left to stop the ball.

SIX! High and handsome! This young man continues to impress. Loopy and full, around leg, Abdullah Shafique shimmies down the track and launches it over long on for a maximum. 50 comes up for Pakistan!
Fuller and around leg, flicked to square leg.

Appeal for a run out, it's referred upstairs... Loopy and full, spinning back in from the rough outside off, Abdullah Shafique opts for the slog-sweep but miscues it in the air. It's timed badly and doesn't carry to the fielder in the deep. Cameron Green fires in the throw to the keeper who takes the bails off. Marnus Labuschagne sees Imam-ul-Haq jumping and thinks that he is in the air when the bails come off. It's referred upstairs and the replays find that Imam had jumps after getting inside the crease.
This time Abdullah Shafique gets forward and flicks it well but finds short mid-wicket.
Not a lot of turn on this one as it lands on the fuller side around off, Abdullah Shafique leans forward to flick but gets a soft leading edge towards covers.
A touch short and outside off, turning back into the batter, Abdullah Shafique pushes it from the back foot to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq goes on the back foot and cuts it down to deep backward point for a couple.
Slows it up in the air, full and around off, Imam tries to defend off the front foot but misses and is pinged on the pads. The impact is outside the line of the stumps though.
Flighted and full, around off, Imam again uses his feet and jams it down successfully.
Walks forward to a full ball and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, driven against the spin but straight to covers.

FOUR! Beating the full-length dive from Usman Khawaja. Loopy delivery, around off, Imam skips down the track and whips it through the gap between mid on and mid-wicket. Usman Khawaja tries his best but cannot prevent the boundary.
Turning back in from outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the back foot.
Loopy and full, around off, Abdullah Shafique draws forward and defends it ahead of his front pad.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.

Shout for a caught behind! The finger goes up and the batter takes the DRS. Coming to the delivery, it's smart from Lyon. He gets one ball to spin back in a mile and serves a slider on this occasion. Abdullah Shafique walks across a bit and tries to defend with the spin. The ball though skids on and goes closely past the outside edge of his bat. Alex Carey collects and appeals, and the umpire agrees. Abdullah Shafique takes the DRS and the UltraEdge finds nothing.
Loopy and full, around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it by getting forward.

Whoa! There you go. Big spin out of the footmarks. Lyon puts it outside off, landing on rough and it turns back in a mile. Abdullah Shafique offers no shot and then sees it going closely past the off pole.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Imam defends it off the front foot to covers.
Turning down the leg side, it's defended down in front of short leg.
Floated and around off, drifting in, Imam tries to flick but it takes the inside edge and goes to square leg.
Fuller and outside off, driven down to mid off.
A controlled flick shot on this occasion, to a full ball around middle and it travels in the gap at square leg for a run.
Too full in length around middle, Abdullah Shafique hurries down the track and goes hard at it. It takes the inner half and goes to backward square leg.

Drinks! It's been a steady start from the opening pair of Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique as they have remained watchful from the start. But now they have started putting away the bad balls as well. Mitchell Starc and Pat Cummins didn't get much purchase with the hard new ball and even in the first innings, both of them got the softer ball to reverse and got their wickets. Nathan Lyon has troubled the batters at times but hasn't created a clear-cut opportunity yet. There's still 17 overs left in the day's play and the Pakistani dug out will be hoping their openers remain at the crease for the entirety of those 17 overs. Australia will have to believe that they just need one wicket to put all the pressure on the hosts.
Floated and full, around middle and leg, Imam draws forward and defends. Maiden, first from Lyon in his 5 overs.
Again the length is on the shorter side, around off, allowing the batter to go back and deal with it. Imam forces it out to covers.
Misses out! Short and wide outside off, Imam punches it from the back foot but finds the cover fielder.
Identical to the last delivery, this time Imam defends it back from the inner part of his bat.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Imam gets forward and defends it back.
A bit short and on off, spinning away, Imam cuts but finds the backward point fielder.
Short again, spinning in from around off, it's punched back towards the bowler. Swepson doesn't stop cleanly and they cross.
Spinning in from the rough outside off, Imam goes on the back foot and keeps it out towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off, defended back.
Flighted and full, outside off, Imam lunges and defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Perhaps an attempted wrong 'un, on the shorter side around off, Imam rocks back and hammers it towards the fence at mid-wicket.
Too full in length and outside off, it's driven back to the bowler.
Loopy and full, landing outside off, Abdullah Shafique luges and offers a good solid forward defensive shot.
Uses his feet to reach the pitch of the ball and then defends it back to the bowler.
The length is a bit short again, around off and breaking into the batter, Abdullah Shafique turns it down towards backward square leg.
FOUR! Nicely played! Lyon is a bit on the shorter side outside off, Abdullah Shafique buys the width as he rocks back and slaps it through point for a boundary.

Beautifully bowled by Lyon as he senses the charge from the batter. Imam has to reach out and does well to stroke it through cover-point. Starc chases it down and pulls it back before the fence. Saves one run.
Fuller and around off, Imam walks forward and defends it back to the bowler.
A touch short and flat on middle, Abdullah Shafique goes on the back foot and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy and landing full outside off, Imam uses his feet and drives it to mid off for a brisk single.
Spinning into the batter from the rough outside off, fuller in length, Imam defends it.
Flighted one, landing outside off, Imam-ul-Haq goes back and defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up, full and on middle, pushed down towards mid on for a quick run.
Starts with a friendly full toss around off, Abdullah Shafique misses out as he hits it straight to the man at mid on.
Spin from both ends now as Mitchell Swepson is brought into the attack.
Flighted this time, full and on off, Imam strides forward in defense.
Once again the length is a bit short around off, Imam stays back and blocks it down.
Flatter this time, short and on off, defended off the back foot.
Advances down the track, doesn't reach the pitch of the ball completely but still manages to defend it back. Risky.
Short in length on off, turning in, Abdullah Shafique goes back and punches it to covers for a single.
Loopy and full, around leg, Imam-ul-Haq jumps down the track and nudges it in front of square on the leg side for a quick run. A direct hit at the striker's end but Abdullah Shafique is safely in.
Fuller this time, around off, shaping back in, Imam flicks it down to fine leg for a single.
Edged but safe! In the channel around off, angling in from a full length, Imam-ul-Haq tries to push but gets a soft outside edge. It doesn't carry to Cameron Green at second slip.
Fuller and on off, defended watchfully with a high elbow from Imam.
Cummins comes from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball on off, Imam defends it from the back foot.
Fuller this time, on middle, it's helped wide of mid on for a single.
Fractionally short and on off, angling in, Abdullah Shafique works it on the leg side but finds square leg.
A touch flat and around off, Usman Khawaja gets back and defends it from the crease.
Walks down the track to a full ball and knocks it towards mid on.
Aerial but safe! Tossed up, full and around off, Shafique leans forward and across to flick but it takes the upper half of his bat. Goes aerially but safely to mid on and they cross for a run.
Floated and full on middle, Imam tucks it in the gap at mid-wicket and rotates the strike.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. Pat Cummins listens to his players and takes the DRS. Lyon serves it around off, gets it to skid back in with the angle, Imam-ul-Haq presses forward to defend but misses. He is struck on the pads, they appeal but to no avail. The UltraEdge detects a big spike. Australia lose a reveiw.
FOUR! This is one way to tackle spin. Use your feet. Imam wears his skates to take it on the full and forces it down the ground for a boundary at long on.
Returns to bowling full on middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique covers the line and defends it to mid on.
Taps a length ball down to covers and steps out of the crease, in search of a run. Abdullah Shafique is sent back by his partner.
Puts it on a fuller length around off, Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks it to covers.
Cummins is targeting the stumps. A good ploy with the pitch offering uneven bounce. Abdullah Shafique defends this full ball towards mid-wicket.
Goes fuller and on middle, Abdullah Shafique brings his bat down and defends it towards mid on.
Slightly short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the back foot.
Pat Cummins to steam in from the opposite end now. Change of ends for him.
A touch short and on off, skidding in, Imam gets back and defends it down.

Oohhh...this one turns with some extra bounce. Lyon gives it some extra rev. Lands it around off and it spins away, Imam tries to defend but is beaten past the outside edge. It curls and Smith collects it at first slip. This delivery is enough to put a seed of doubt in the mind of the batters.
Nice and full, close to off, Imam is forward with a vertical bat in defense.
Finds the gap! Too full and around off, Imam drills his drive past the diving cover fielder for a couple of runs. Lyon won't mind that shot out of the rough.
Fuller and around off, defended back to the left side of the bowler.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Imam stretches forward and defends it to silly point.
After just 5 overs of play, the visitors opt for spin. Nathan Lyon is introduced into the attack.
Angling away from the batsman, on a good length, Abdullah allows it through to the keeper.
Fuller in length and outside off, Imam drives it to the right of mid off and Swepson makes a tumbling stop. They cross for a single.
Bangs it in around off, this one doesn't get up much, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it from the back foot.
Back of a length, close to off, Imam goes on his toes and drops it down with soft hands to square leg.
This one is a little behind of a fuller length, around off, Imam goes back and plays it down to point. His partner wants a run but is sent back as the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Pitches it up and around off, Imam defends it near his front pad and pushes it down towards mid on.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.

FOUR! Classy! This is a shot of a batsman in prime form! Fuller and around off, Abdullah Shafique anticipates the length early, takes his front foot forward to cover the line and caresses it down through mid on with a lovely followthrough of his bat.
Lands it full and on off, getting it to angle in, Abdullah Shafique is very solid in his forward defense.
Keeps it full and on off, blocked solidly to mid off.
Full again, around off, defended back towards the bowler. Cummins failed to collect it and it went on to hit the stumps at the other end.
Fuller and around off at 140.8 kph, Abdullah Shafique defends it watchfully towards mid off.
Bowls it with a slingy action and fails to control the line. This one goes down the leg side and troubles Carey more than Imam. A good take by the Aussie keeper.
Excellent yorker, around middle at 144.3 kph, Imam-ul-Haq keeps his eyes glued to the ball and does well to dig it out safely.
Fuller again, around off, Imam gets across and pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller and on middle, Imam tries to play with a dead bat but it takes the inner edge and runs down through backward square leg. They take two - first runs off the bat.
Full in length and slipping down the leg side, Imam tries to buy some cheap runs off his pads but doesn't succeed.
Starc keeps this one a length and close to off, Imam-ul-Haq covers the line and movement as he blocks it to the leg side.
Pitches it on a length and keeps it around off, Abdullah Shafique covers the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
Outside off, the batter is not interested in playing at that.
In the channel outside off, on a good length and it has good bounce and carry, Abdullah Shafique allows it through to the keeper.

Howzzat? Cummins angles in a length ball around leg, Abdullah Shafique tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to fine leg and the bowler appeals. Nothing from the umpire. Missing leg. They take a couple of leg byes.
Delivers it in the zone outside off, skidding off the surface, Abdullah Shafique lets it be.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Abdullah defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Pat Cummins to steam in from the opposite end.
In the channel outside off, on a good length and shaping away, Imam-ul-Haq shoulders arms.
Spears it full and on middle at 144.1 kph, Imam keeps it out safely to mid on.
Starc is unable to control the movement again. Slips it down the leg side, the batter leaves and Carey only makes a partial stop. Pakistan are off the mark with a bye!
Inswinger again, but down the leg side, Abdullah Shafique tries to flick but misses once more.
Appeal for an lbw, the umpire remains unmoved. This one starts from a length around leg and is moving down, Abdullah Shafique tries to flick but misses. No DRS taken, possibly going down leg.
Starc begins with a full ball in the channel outside off, Abdullah Shafique allows it through to the keeper.
